    <h1 id="title">Hello Kitty</h1>
    <p>The Kitty Who Stole the Hearts of Millions</p>
      <figure id="img-div">
        <img id="image" src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/sanrio/images/9/9f/Hello_Kitty.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/1200?cb=20191128154539" alt="Hello Kitty seen in pink dress and with pink hairbow standing and waving left paw">
        <figcaption id="img-caption">Hello Kitty was born in the suburbs of London. She lives with her parents and her twin sister Mimmy who is her best friend.
        </figcaption>
     </figure>
     <section id="tribute-info">
       <h3 id="headline">How Hello Kitty took the World by storm:</h3>
       <ul>
         <li>
           <strong>1974</strong>
           - Character created by Ikuko Shimizu, a designer for Sanrio
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>1975</strong>
           - Earns name "Haro-Kiti" or "Hello Kitty" in English and dons blue overalls
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>1978</strong>
           - Sanrio begins to distribute products across Europe and debuts the first Hello Kitty digital watch two years later with a over a million sold
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>1992</strong>
           - Pink is unveiled as the primary color palette for Hello Kitty
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>1999</strong>
           - Hello Kitty turns 25 and gets a boyfriend, Dear Daniel. He boasts an impressive white tuft of hair, is also a Brit, and likes to "take photos of animals"
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>2003</strong>
           - The Spring/Summer 2003 collection from Heatherette is Hello Kitty's first designer collaboration on the runway
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>2005</strong>
           - Kimora Lee Simmons debuts the first high-end Hello Kitty diamond jewelery collection
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>2010</strong>
           - Sephora launches original Hello Kitty line with eye shadow palletes, lip gloss, perfume, and more
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>2013</strong>
           - Eva Air unveils new 777 Hello Kitty Jet
         </li>
         <li>
           <strong>2014</strong>
           - Sanrio reveals Hello Kitty is not a cat...she is a little girl
         </li>
       </ul>
       <blockquote cite="https://www.sanrio.com/collections/hello-kitty">
        <p>"You can never have too many friends!"</p>
        <cite>--Hello Kitty</cite>
        <h3>If you would like to know more about Hello Kitty or any of the other Sanrio characters, please visit the <a id="tribute-link" href="https://www.sanrio.com" target="_blank"> Sanrio site.</a></h3>
     </section>
